<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Evaluate/Prevention</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">Before calibrating the printheads make sure the filling procedure was successful, and no air is present in the printheads.
</p></section><section id="GUID-02CACDE2-0BC5-4166-B59A-075FDE7A1B9C" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Background info</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">This calibration is used to set the correct PAINt-reference values so NFC will work correctly. A failure during this calibration is mainly caused when the nozzles are not filled correctly, and air is disturbing the jet-behaviour.
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-F2864082-F34C-4657-B37E-EA7C5343FE90.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
